\begin{split}&\displaystyle\int_{\mathbb{R}}\frac{1-\cos Tx}{x^{2}}(F(x+a)-G(x%
+a))dx\\
\displaystyle\leq&\displaystyle-2M\Delta\int_{0}^{\Delta}\frac{1-\cos Tx}{x^{2%
}}dx+4M\Delta\int_{\Delta}^{\infty}\frac{1-\cos Tx}{x^{2}}dx\\
\displaystyle=&\displaystyle 2M\Delta\left(-3\int_{0}^{\Delta}\frac{1-\cos Tx}%
{x^{2}}dx+2\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{1-\cos Tx}{x^{2}}dx\right)\\
\displaystyle=&\displaystyle 2M\Delta\left(-3\int_{0}^{\Delta}\frac{1-\cos Tx}%
{x^{2}}dx+2\cdot\frac{\pi T}{2}\right)\\
\displaystyle=&\displaystyle 2MT\Delta\left(-3\int_{0}^{T\Delta}\frac{1-\cos x%
}{x^{2}}dx+\pi\right),\end{split}

para.p:
We finally prove the Berry-Esseen theorem.
